Misc

Source: vignettes/Misc.Rmd
Misc.Rmd

Apart form /table and /schema, there is also support for the simple endpoints /info and /rate_limit.

sc_info()
##   locale displayName
## 1     de     Deutsch
## 2     en     English
sc_rate_limit()
## remaining: 95/100
## reset:     2021-02-15 10:25:09

Rate limits can also be obtained from the response of the /table endpoint with sc_table_rate_limit()

table <- sc_table(sc_example("bev_seit_1982.json"))
sc_table_rate_limit(table)
## remaining: 95/100
## reset:     2021-02-15 10:25:09

STATcube uses caching for the /table endpoint by default. If the same request to sc_post_json() is sent several times, this will not count towards the rate-limit (100 requests per hour).
